1.title: Working K-9 to 5
1.plot: Dolores has to prove to her dad that she is responsible enough to adopt a puppy, so she becomes a delivery girl for his newspaper. The Pound Puppies investigate why her deliveries are taking long, so they can match her to her perfect pup.

2.title: Cuddle Up Buttercup
2.plot: A puppy named Buttercup looks so identical to the latest toy sensation, Cuddle Up Buttercup, that kids think that she is really toy. The Pound Puppies scramble to find her perfect person before she gets nabbed.

3.title: The Pups Who Loved Me
3.plot: British Pound Puppy agent Bondo arrives at Shelter 17 in his flying car. While playing in the car, the Super Secret Pup Club set off the controls and fly to London.

4.title: Fright at the Museum
4.plot: The Pound Puppies sneak into a museum to place Millie with Amelia, the curator's granddaughter. Niblet and Squirt then run into a revived cat mummy named Meowtuhotep.

5.title: Puddles the Problem Pup
5.plot: The Pound Puppies are ready to place Puddles with his perfect person, but Puddles isn't housebroken yet. They try various ways to potty-train him, but his person Sam may have the solution.

6.title: It's Elementary My Dear Pup Club
6.plot: When Chucky gets in trouble at school for drawing in permanent marker on school white boards, Pepper and the Pup Club investigate to see who's really responsible.

7.title: Hot Dawg
7.plot: In this series, the mission of a team of fearless dogs is to find homes for puppies in need. Their motto is "A pup for every person and a person for every pup." The Pound Puppies appear to be "average dogs" keeping the humans who are running Shelter 17 in the dark while helping "dog-kind" find loving families. Once you're a Pound Puppy, you're always a Pound Puppy.

11.title: Hello Kitten
11.plot: The Super Secret Pup Club take over an adoption mission from the Kennel Kittens, to get Spoons to her perfect person, due to Ace's overconfidence.

12.title: Beauty Is Only Fur Deep
12.plot: A heroic rescue dog arrives at the shelter without any fur; Squirt makes him a full-body toupee, but the pup's lack of confidence makes it difficult to find him the perfect home.

13.title: The Watchdogs
13.plot: Strudel begins leading a double life after being mistaken for a superhero, but her new job threatens her position on the team.

14.title: Hail to the Chief
14.plot: Agent Ping challenges Strudel to find the perfect home for rambunctious pup Chief. Strudel eagerly accepts until she finds out that Chief's perfect home is with the President's daughters.

15.title: All Bark and Little Bite
15.plot: Two of Patches' old friends tease him for hanging out with girl pups.

16.title: Lucky the Dunce
16.plot: Lucky comes up with this ingenious plot to get a handful of pups adopted but doesn't tell the whole plot to his team. While the plan goes into action, something goes wrong, and Strudel's machine winded up zapping Lucky in the head causing him to act like a moron. Now, Niblet has a new friend in Lucky while the others try as fast as they can to get Lucky back to normal.

23.title: Lord of the Fleas
23.plot: The Pound Puppies trick Agatha into taking her yacht out for a cruise so they can get Solo to his new owner, but Solo is not interested; he just wants to go adventuring. They wind up getting stranded on an uncharted island. Agatha, Olaf and McLeash go on the island to find help, Solo goes off to find adventure on the island, the Pound Puppies go to look for Solo. They later find out there is an active volcano on the island and must hurry to get off.

25.title: The Pupple's Court
25.plot: Lucky's habit of following instinct over rules lands him in front of a Pound Puppy tribunal that could mean the end of Shelter 17 if he is found guilty.

1.title: The Yipper Caper
1.plot: When a seemingly unmatchable pup meets, then loses, the boy of his dreams, it's up to the Pound Puppies to do what they do best.

2.title: Nightmare on Pound Street
2.plot: It's Halloween, and McLeish has to take chaperone his bratty niece and nephew. Meanwhile, the Pound Puppies have to place a sweet but scary-looking dog.

3.title: Rebound
3.plot: The Pound Puppies have to find a home for the overly-energetic Rebound.

4.title: The General
4.plot: The mysterious Pound Puppy General arrives at the shelter with a daunting task for Lucky and the gang.

5.title: The Prince and the Pupper
5.plot: Feeling unappreciated, Squirt switches places with an aristocratic dog who looks exactly like him.

6.title: Catcalls
6.plot: It's the Pound Puppies vs. The Kennel Kitties as they each try to place one of their own in a home that only wants either a dog or a cat.

7.title: King of the Heap
7.plot: During a mix-up at the pound, Niblet is mistakenly adopted as the new junkyard dog.

8.title: My Fair Rebound
8.plot: Ms. McLeish wants to enter Rebound in a dog show to show up a rival and her upper class canine. Believing that she must repay her owner for adopting her, Rebound seeks help from the Pound Puppies to help her become a proper contestant.

9.title: Quintuplets
9.plot: The Pound Puppies are challenged with the task of finding a home for five puppies who don't want to be separated from each other.

10.title: Dog on a Wire
10.plot: The Pound Puppies return a circus dog that got left behind, but when they get to the Big Top, Strudel remembers her dream of being a performance dog.

11.title: Homeward Pound
11.plot: After a mission at an airport, Squirt and Niblet get taken to Canada by accident and have to find their way home.

12.title: Rebel Without a Collar
12.plot: Cookie develops a crush on a coyote who comes to the pound disguised as a dog. Cookie considers leaving the pound to live in the wild with her new crush.

13.title: Taboo
13.plot: It's up to the Pound Puppies to find a home for a dog who is convinced he's nothing but bad luck.

14.title: Toyoshiko! Bark Friend Machine
14.plot: When a robot dog named Toyoshiko comes to the pound, Strudel finally meets someone who understands her.

15.title: Zoltron
15.plot: Zoltron has been separated from his family during an outing. He seeks help from the gang to be reunited with his family?who may or may not be from Earth!

16.title: The Really Weird Dog
16.plot: Rover seeks the help of Lucky and his gang to find his person. But Rover is not just any ordinary dog; in fact, he's not a dog at all.

17.title: Bone Voyage
17.plot: When Agitha McLeish leaves to go on vacation, she leaves Rebound behind at the pound. Rebound tries to follow her, fearing abandonment.

18.title: Snow Problem
18.plot: The Pound Puppies join a dog sled race to help Tundra, a Siberian Husky puppy, meet his perfect person.

19.title: The K9 Kid
19.plot: The Pound Puppies meet Pepper, who wants to be a police dog, but she isn't the right breed or size for the job. Can she prove she has what it takes?

20.title: The Call of the Squirrel Dog
20.plot: Squirt tells the story of how Mr. Nut Nut, the squirrel, joined the Pound Puppies.

21.title: I Never Barked for My Father
21.plot: Niblet brings a new pup and his older pal to the shelter to hide from a dogcatcher - and Lucky has to deal with some family ties.

22.title: Mcleish Unleashed
22.plot: Milton Feltwaddle returns to Shelter 17, taking over and causing problems for the Pound Puppies' operations.

23.title: Olaf in Love
23.plot: A new puppy believes that she has found the perfect person for Olaf and Gertrude the librarian, so it's up to the Pound Puppies to get the two to realize that they are made for each other and get Kiki a forever home.

24.title: Kennel Kittens Return
24.plot: When the Kennel Kittens steal Strudel's new invention, Squirt goes undercover as a cat to retrieve it.

25.title: Mutternal Instincts
25.plot: Lucky and the gang are dumfounded when it's revealed that Cookie has been trying to prevent a pup from getting adopted!

26.title: Lucky Gets Adopted
26.plot: Lucky is adopted against his will by an eccentric social outcast named Dot. However, his new owner's overaffectionate and pushy ways make him uncomfortable. Will he reveal the Pound Puppies' secret?

1.title: Zipper the Zoomit Dog
1.plot: Squirt reveals his secret past and vows to train Zipper to catch flying discs.

2.title: The Fraud Princess
2.plot: Agatha's new beau brings a nosy playmate over for Rebound.

3.title: The Super Secret Pup Club
3.plot: In this series, the mission of a team of fearless dogs is to find homes for puppies in need. Their motto is "A pup for every person and a person for every pup." The Pound Puppies appear to be "average dogs" keeping the humans who are running Shelter 17 in the dark while helping "dog-kind" find loving families. Once you're a Pound Puppy, you're always a Pound Puppy.

4.title: Barlow
4.plot: Barlow preaches on a philosophy of laziness, which the other dogs at Shelter 17 are eager to embrace.

5.title: There's Something About Camelia
5.plot: A dog named Camelia matches well with many people, so the puppies try to find her best match.

6.title: Good Dog, McLeish!
6.plot: McLeish is accidentally hypnotized into thinking he is a dog.

7.title: The Ruff Ruff Bunch
7.plot: While the Pound Puppies search for the missing dog Cuddlesworth, the Super Secret Pup Club are initiated into a fancy dog club led by a mysterious founder.

8.title: Salty
8.plot: Salty, an ailing sea dog, tries to choose his own replacement.

9.title: Squawk
9.plot: Niblet spills the Pound Puppies' secrets to a new parrot at the pound who escapes and begins blabbing top secret information to the humans.

10.title: The Accidental Pup Star
10.plot: Rebound is caught singing a song in an online video, and the Pound Puppies have to prevent McLeish from using this to become famous, as well as discredit the fact that dogs can talk.

11.title: No Dogs Allowed
11.plot: The Pound Puppies investigate why people are returning their pups to the pound and find that the landlord of an apartment has a no-dogs-allowed policy.

12.title: Pound Preemies
12.plot: A dog named Petunia gives premature birth to a litter of puppies at Shelter 17, who are mistakenly adopted by a trio of girls. The Pound Puppies must find the newborns and get them back to their mother.

13.title: I Heard the Barks on Christmas Eve
13.plot: The Pound Puppies need a miracle to place thousands of puppies that are overflowing from shelters all over town. The task seems insurmountable, but Rebound's tenacity may be just enough to pull off a Christmas miracle.
